!! Helper: `tw-upload`

A standalone CLI tool for uploading binary files to a running MCP server via named pipe. It handles authentication, base64 encoding, and the MCP protocol automatically.

!!! Usage

```
node tw-upload.js <file> [--wiki <path>] [--title <title>] [--tags <tags>] [--subfolder <dir>]
```

|!Option |!Description |
|`<file>` |File to upload (PNG, JPG, GIF, PDF — max 50MB) |
|`--wiki <path>` |Wiki directory to find `.tw-mcp/connect` (defaults to current dir) |
|`--title <title>` |Tiddler title (defaults to filename) |
|`--tags <tags>` |Space-separated tags (use `[[double brackets]]` for multi-word tags) |
|`--subfolder <dir>` |Subfolder within `files/` to save to |

!!! Examples

```
node tw-upload.js photo.png --wiki ./editions/tw5.com
node tw-upload.js doc.pdf --title "My Document" --tags "docs reference"
node tw-upload.js icon.gif --subfolder images --tags "[[site images]]"
```

> The MCP server must be running. If the `.tw-mcp/connect` file is missing, `tw-upload` will show a clear error with the command to start the server.

